    },
    {
        "BTR-152": "Btr-152"
    },
    {
        ", were used, some of which lacked overhead protection and were therefore vulnerable to artillery fire. It still gave the Soviet Army greater strategic flexibility because of the large land area and the long borders of the Soviet Union and its allies in the ": null
    },
    {
        "Warsaw Pact": "Warsaw Pact"
    },
    {
        ".     The US Army established the basic configuration of the tracked APC with the ": null
    },
