        " . Such vehicles are usually expedients, and lack of space prevents the armament of an IFV being carried in addition to an infantry section or squad. In the Russian Army, such vehicles were introduced for fighting in urban areas, where the risk from short range infantry anti-tank weapons, such as the ": null
    },
    {
        "RPG-7": "Rpg-7"
    },
    {
        ", is highest, after Russian tank and motor infantry units suffered heavy losses fighting insurgents in ": null
    },
